parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors can cause the steering wheel to vibrate when braking, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Steering wheel vibration when braking
especially at high speeds
uneven brake pad wear
grinding or loud noises when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Noisy brakes can be a sign of worn or faulty brake components, which can lead to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Unusual noises when applying the brakes
such as grinding or screeching sounds
poor brake response
uneven brake pad wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
brakes lock up or pulse when applied
uneven brake pad wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a frontal crash can increase the risk of serious injury or death to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Airbag failure to deploy during a frontal crash
despite meeting the deployment threshold
resulting in potential harm to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corroded Front Sub-Frame Causing Suspension and Steering Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the front sub-frame can lead to a loss of structural integrity, causing the suspension and steering components to malfunction, which can result in a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the vehicle wanders from side to side while driving
loud banging noise from the front of the vehicle
difficulty shifting into gear
failure to move in reverse or drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lower Suspension Arm Failure Due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower suspension arm due to corrosion can cause the suspension and steering components to malfunction, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the vehicle wanders from side to side while driving
loud banging noise from the front of the vehicle
difficulty shifting into gear
failure to move in reverse or drive.
